# Check every text file out with LF, on every platform.
#
# Without this, git's Windows default (`core.autocrlf=true`) rewrites LF to CRLF
# on checkout — and files hrdr *embeds* come along for the ride. The system prompt
# is `include_str!`d from `templates/system.j2`, so a Windows build shipped a
# prompt whose every line ended `\r\n`: different bytes to the model than every
# other platform sends, and three prompt tests that match across a line break
# failed there and only there (the `Build` job is gated on the tests, so the
# v0.3.0 release never published).
#
# The rendered prompt is data, not source — it should not depend on the OS the
# binary was built on.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Anything embedded in the binary or compared byte-for-byte is LF, always.
*.j2 text eol=lf
*.rs text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf

# Binary: never touched.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
